Creating images with R

with a little bit of magick

Elizabeth Wu

2023-03-11

My meme

My meme details my personal experience in the struggles in trying to get my license. 

library(magick)

#top right square and text
text1 <- image_blank(width = 300,
            height = 288,
            color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "My driving instructor telling me\nexactly what went wrong\nand what needs to be done",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 20,
                 font = "Calibri",
                 gravity = "center")

#bottom right square and text
text2 <- image_blank(width = 300,
                     height = 400,
                     color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Them watching me\nfail for the 4th time",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 20,
                 font = "Calibri",
                 gravity = "center")

#cat images on left
cat_reading <- image_read("https://pbs.twimg.com/media/EMIOvSXWsAoPwtv.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(300)
confusion <- image_read("https://ih1.redbubble.net/image.949021450.7413/flat,750x,075,f-pad,750x1000,f8f8f8.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(300)

#combining first image and top text for the top row
top_pics <- c(cat_reading, text1)
top_row <- image_append(top_pics)

#combining second image and bottom text for the bottom row
bottom_pics <- c(confusion, text2)
bottom_row <- image_append(bottom_pics)

#combined final meme
final_meme <- c(top_row, bottom_row) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)

#exporting meme
image_write(final_meme, "final_meme.png")

My animated GIF

My animated GIF involves a happy dancing banana. 

library(magick)

# creates a vector for the counts
counts <- 1 : 4 %>% as.character()

# loads the main banana image
banana <- image_read("https://static.vecteezy.com/system/resources/previews/005/658/143/original/banana-character-with-happy-emotion-joyful-face-smile-eyes-arms-and-legs-person-with-expression-fruit-emoticon-flat-illustration-vector.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(1000)


# sets up a blank rectangle with text in each colour
red_text <- image_blank(width = 1000,
                        height = 100,
                        color = "black") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "DANCING BANANA", color = "red", boxcolor = "black", size = 100, gravity = "center")

orange_text <- image_blank(width = 1000,
                           height = 100,
                           color = "black") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "DANCING BANANA", color = "orange", boxcolor = "black", size = 100, gravity = "center")

yellow_text <- image_blank(width = 1000,
                           height = 100,
                           color = "black") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "DANCING BANANA", color = "yellow", boxcolor = "black", size = 100, gravity = "center")

green_text <- image_blank(width = 1000,
                          height = 100,
                          color = "black") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "DANCING BANANA", color = "green", boxcolor = "black", size = 100, gravity = "center")


# combines each element into its own vector and appends it vertically
frame1 <- image_append(c(red_text, banana, red_text), stack = TRUE)
frame2 <- image_append(c(orange_text, image_flop(banana), orange_text), stack = TRUE)
frame3 <- image_append(c(yellow_text, banana, yellow_text), stack = TRUE)
frame4 <- image_append(c(green_text, image_flip(banana), green_text), stack = TRUE)

# final frames
complete_frames <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4)

# creates the animation
final_gif <- image_animate(complete_frames, fps = 5)

#exporting the GIF
image_write(final_gif, "final_animation.gif")
